      "role": "user",
      "content": "but u said the \"primary driver\" is the disincentive effect. if that's the case, doesn't that mean these welfare programs are actually doing more harm to the economy than good? if the main result is less people working, shouldn't we be looking at scaling them back instead of expanding them?",
